Interact with Frappe Cloud for deployment and management.

Authenticate with Frappe Cloud and deploy your apps directly
from the command line.

Examples:
  weg cloud login              # Authenticate with Frappe Cloud
  weg cloud sites              # List your sites
  weg cloud deploy             # Deploy to a site
  weg cloud logs               # View site logs
  weg cloud status             # Check deployment status

Usage:
  weg cloud [command]

Available Commands:
  benches     List your Frappe Cloud benches
  deploy      Deploy to Frappe Cloud
  login       Authenticate with Frappe Cloud
  logout      Log out from Frappe Cloud
  logs        View site logs from Frappe Cloud
  marketplace Manage your Frappe Cloud marketplace apps
  sites       List your Frappe Cloud sites
  status      Check cloud account, site, or job status

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for cloud

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg cloud [command] --help" for more information about a command.
